The obvious thing to do isn't this. The monster just let out a screech and tried to charge straight at Sasaal. Luckily, Sasaal may be big, but he's still pretty agile, and dodged out of the way just in time. However, Nixi still can't help but scream, almost slipping off Sasaal's smooth scales in the process.
"How do we kill them?" Nixi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"This is too hard!"
Sasaal let out a screech, circled once, and flew towards the mountain he called home. The black monster followed close behind, but when it was hit with flames from behind, it seemed a bit disoriented. This monster hadn't realized it had another opponent yet. Sasaal slowed down, then used his tail to strike the monster's head, knocking it off course, and the monster became even more disoriented.
The monster let out a fierce roar, with a screeching sound in its throat, flying straight up in the air while spewing out something from its mouth. Suddenly, the surrounding area became pitch black as if the monster was absorbing the light from the sky, replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasaal's eyes went black, and he tried to retreat, but ended up crashing into a tree branch and falling onto the open ground. The monster seemed to know exactly where Sasaal landed, flying straight towards him and bringing the dark cloud with it.
"Kayerl!" Tenuk shouted, flying out of the cloud as he began to circle, searching for Nixi and Sasaal in the darkness below. "What do we do? Kayerl...? Kayerl, where are you?"
Nixi struggled to her feet. She was certain she had broken her bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability was already kicking in. Sasaal's situation was different; he lay weakly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked over. Nixi endeavored to make her way to Sasaal, but her vision was obscured by the pitch blackness, and she could barely see anything. Everywhere were terrifying shadows, and something was screaming in the shadows.
A terrifying club-like tail suddenly slammed into the ground, sending Nixi tumbling to the ground. She noticed the tail was wildly flailing, but the target didn't seem to be her. Nixi managed to see that the monster was roaring, using its claws to frantically scratch at the shadows it had created. Something was teleporting through the darkness, waiting for the perfect moment to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot rang out, breaking the air, and the monster instantly became quiet, lying on the ground motionless. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the true situation. Kayerl stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, panting heavily.
"That is... this is one of the most bizarre shadow leaps I've done... Tantot Cartelion...” Kayerl said, gasping for breath. For some reason, his eyes flashed with black light, and a dark energy was surging within him. But just as Kayerl opened his mouth to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
After a while, Nixi understood what had happened. They all knew that Kayerl possessed a strange shadow ability, but he rarely used it because most people thought it was extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nixi did not know that Kayerl could use this ability in any darkness. And from Kayerl's appearance, he was also very surprised.
"You're okay?" Nixi couldn't help but ask.
"I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon." Kayerl looked at his "masterpiece," and at that time, Tenuk landed beside him, returning to his original Sbast form.
Now, the monster stopped moving, and they could take a good look at it. Its skin was dark and shiny, covered with a layer of sticky liquid that stuck firmly to its body. It had four wings and four legs, each leg ending with long, thin claws, and two straight horns on its skull.
Tenuk and Kayerl hadn't even had time to ask what it was when another monster suddenly leaped out of the nearby bushes, screaming. Just then, a familiar car crashed into the side of the monster, and it slid to a stop at Nixi's feet. Nixi didn't hesitate, grabbed her shotgun, and shot the monster right between the eyes, killing it instantly.
"Oh no...” Reetwvic muttered from the driver's seat, then clumsily turned off the engine and climbed out of the car. "Uh, I didn't mean to. Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the good parts!” Tenuk said, shaking his head. "Where did you go?"
"You guys left me behind. I rushed back as fast as I could...” Reetwvic sighed. "Excuse me, but what are these terrifying things?"
Reetwvic's question was answered by Sasaal, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, and looked a bit dizzy, but the wounds didn't seem to be too serious.
“You killed the Corrupted ones! Those infected monsters. When the Corrupted attacked your god, these creatures were left behind.”
“You mean... we... helped kill the terrifying Monster God?” Tenuk stuttered slightly.
“Yes, indeed. There may be more Corrupted ones, but I couldn't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun, and it's also unfair to fight one on one, right?” Sasaal walked up to Kayerl and patted his head. “Thanks, little one. You reminded me of my old friend Arkindin. Only you're not as ruthless, and you don't have his ability to destroy the universe.”
“Uh... thanks... I think...” Kayerl shrugged his shoulders. “So, uh, did we complete the mission?”
Nixi shrugged her shoulders, picked up her camera, and took a few photos of the definitely dead monsters. Then, she pulled out her favorite dagger - the exquisite Death God Dagger - and began to cut apart one of the monster's horns, and then another. However, just as Nixi finished cutting, the monsters suddenly began to self-ignite and turned into a pile of ashes in no time. Nixi's cut horns also turned to ashes.
"Well... this is a double-edged sword..." Nixi let out a sigh. "At least I have some photos, right?"
